The paper deals with image denoising, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. The proposed method involves using group sparsity residual and external nonlocal self-similarity prior to improve the denoising performance. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of Gaussian Mixture model (GMM) learning and group sparse coefficients suggests that the paper may also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of external prior information and the focus on image processing also suggest that the paper may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories.
